13760353.review:
Ok, let's be a bit structured:

Pros:

- Good Point'n'Click humour in the spirit of a "classic" game (Simon the Sorcerer/Monkey Island);
- The story is enjoyable, and so are the characters;
- It is pretty long for a Point'n'Click (getting all the dialogue options and finishing the game took me about 20 hours);
- Many references to pop culture, especially MedFan universes;
- It isn't as simplistic/easy/obvious as a TellTale Point'n'Click... In my opinion !
- The voice acting is cool!

Cons:

- Graphics are not THAT good, even though the fact did not affect my gaming experience;
- Some parts of the game, especially at the beginning, are a bit easy;
- The end of the plot felt a bit rushed to me.


In a nutshell: if you feel nostalgic about good ol'LucasArts Point'n'Clicks, this game may be for you! I'm personally a big fan of Monkey Island / Sam and Max: Hit the Road,... and I found the game very enjoyable.

